Middle English <i>ston(e)</i> ‘stone’ + <i>-er</i>, used for someone who lived by a prominent rock or stone, or perhaps who came from a place called Stone, although this formation is more rare. See   Stone   and compare   Stoneman  .","Americanized form (translation into English) of German   Steiner  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Stone","meanings":["English: from Middle English <i>ston(e)</i> ‘stone, rock’ (Old English <i>stān</i>). The surname may be topographic, for someone who lived on stony ground, by a notable outcrop of rock, or by a stone boundary-marker or monument, or habitational, from a place called Stone, such as those in Buckinghamshire, Devon, Gloucestershire, Hampshire, Kent, Somerset, Staffordshire, and Worcestershire.","Irish (Kilkenny): adopted for Irish <b>Ó Clochartaigh</b> (see   Clougherty  ) and/or <b>Ó Clochasaigh</b> (see   Clohessy  ), and possibly several other names containing or thought to contain the element <i>cloch</i> ‘stone’.","Americanized form (translation into English) of various surnames in other languages, meaning ‘stone’, including Jewish   Stein  , Norwegian <b>Steine</b>, French   Lapierre  ."]}]},{"name":"Catherine","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."],"variants":[{"name":"Catheryn","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Katherine","meanings":["Variant of   Katherine ."]},{"name":"Catharin","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Cathrine","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Cathryn","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Cathrin","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Catharine","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":7,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Catherine Stoner was born in 1375, in Norfolk, England as the daughter of Ralph Stoner. She married Thomas Barnes about 1409, in Writtle, Essex, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1442, in Essex, England, at the age of 67."},"et":{"1375–1442":"1375–1442","1360–1440":"1360–1440","1410–1434":"1410–1434","1416–1465":"1416–1465","1350–1395":"1350–1395","about 1409":"umbes 1409","1434":"1434","1410":"1410","1465":"1465","1442":"1442","1375":"1375","1440":"1440","1395":"1395","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","1416":"1416","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England","Writtle, Chelmsford, Essex, England":"Writtle, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Essex, England":"Essex, England"},"fi":{"1375–1442":"1375–1442","1360–1440":"1360–1440","1410–1434":"1410–1434","1416–1465":"1416–1465","1350–1395":"1350–1395","about 1409":"noin 1409","1434":"1434","1410":"1410","1465":"1465","1442":"1442","1375":"1375","1440":"1440","1395":"1395","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","1416":"1416","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England","Writtle, Chelmsford, Essex, England":"Writtle, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England","Essex, England":"Essex, England"},"fr":{"1375–1442":"1375–1442","1360–1440":"1360–1440","1410–1434":"1410–1434","1416–1465":"1416–1465","1350–1395":"1350–1395","about 1409":